1
00:00:00,333 --> 00:00:01,366
welcome back

2
00:00:01,366 --> 00:00:04,833
today we are going to enter the LuV tier

3
00:00:05,066 --> 00:00:05,666
to do that

4
00:00:05,666 --> 00:00:09,400
the first thing we have to do is build an assembly line

5
00:00:09,533 --> 00:00:13,000
this is a multi block which is rather complex to use

6
00:00:13,300 --> 00:00:16,266
but let's start by crafting its parts

7
00:00:16,533 --> 00:00:19,666
crafting those components is not easy nor cheap

8
00:00:19,666 --> 00:00:23,400
and even our automatic crafting system has issues with it

9
00:00:23,500 --> 00:00:24,800
the main problem is that

10
00:00:24,800 --> 00:00:29,133
we do not have a crafting unit capable of handling that amount of materials

11
00:00:29,133 --> 00:00:31,866
so we first make some more storage

12
00:00:32,300 --> 00:00:35,266
we should also make some crafting co-processor

13
00:00:35,266 --> 00:00:37,333
to speed up the crafting process

14
00:00:37,866 --> 00:00:41,900
and once we have added some new and more powerful crafting units

15
00:00:41,900 --> 00:00:45,800
we can finally start working on our assembly line parts

16
00:00:46,200 --> 00:00:48,266
this is going to take some time

17
00:00:48,266 --> 00:00:49,866
so we can do some other things

18
00:00:49,866 --> 00:00:52,333
such as farming withers while we wait

19
00:00:52,633 --> 00:00:55,133
we will need those nether stars later on

20
00:00:55,600 --> 00:00:58,033
however after our brief hunting

21
00:00:58,033 --> 00:00:58,900
we find out that

22
00:00:58,900 --> 00:01:01,866
our crafting system hasn't made much progress

23
00:01:02,400 --> 00:01:04,266
and the main issue seems to be that

24
00:01:04,266 --> 00:01:07,000
our processor can't keep up with all the items

25
00:01:07,000 --> 00:01:09,900
it has to move around the various machines

26
00:01:10,333 --> 00:01:13,000
we could increase the amount of co-processors

27
00:01:13,033 --> 00:01:17,700
but the best solution is to reduce the amount of tasks our processor has to do

28
00:01:18,400 --> 00:01:21,633
we can multiply the amount of materials in the patterns

29
00:01:21,633 --> 00:01:22,133
so that

30
00:01:22,133 --> 00:01:25,733
instead of moving 64 times one dust to the furnace

31
00:01:25,733 --> 00:01:29,033
the processor will just move a stack of dusts once

32
00:01:29,800 --> 00:01:31,266
and while at it

33
00:01:31,266 --> 00:01:34,300
we can also equip our furnace with better coils

34
00:01:34,300 --> 00:01:36,866
so that it will cook more stuff at once

35
00:01:37,700 --> 00:01:41,066
after editing the patterns and restarting the crafting job

36
00:01:41,066 --> 00:01:42,733
we can see the difference in the speed

37
00:01:42,733 --> 00:01:45,733
at which items are being moved to the machines

38
00:01:47,000 --> 00:01:49,200
and after not much time

39
00:01:49,200 --> 00:01:52,233
we can see that our crafting processes are idling

40
00:01:52,800 --> 00:01:53,700
the reason is that

41
00:01:53,700 --> 00:01:58,066
we are crafting thousands of SMD components in a small assembler

42
00:01:58,333 --> 00:01:59,833
16 at a time

43
00:02:00,466 --> 00:02:03,500
and each batch also takes quite some time

44
00:02:04,533 --> 00:02:07,666
we have already split the load across different assemblers

45
00:02:07,700 --> 00:02:10,266
but it doesn't make a noticeable difference

46
00:02:10,600 --> 00:02:14,400
even though four assemblers should be four times faster than one

47
00:02:15,333 --> 00:02:17,433
we could use a higher tier assembler

48
00:02:17,433 --> 00:02:20,433
but the power consumption would grow exponentially

49
00:02:20,933 --> 00:02:22,633
so we need a multi block

50
00:02:23,033 --> 00:02:24,933
the first option is the gregtech ++ one

51
00:02:25,600 --> 00:02:30,200
but that requires ZPM stuff that we don't have access to yet

52
00:02:30,533 --> 00:02:35,700
the second option is to parallelize a stack of assemblers inside a processing array

53
00:02:36,233 --> 00:02:37,000
however

54
00:02:37,000 --> 00:02:38,633
that machine doesn't scale well 

55
00:02:38,633 --> 00:02:41,066
when we will need to further upgrade it

56
00:02:42,066 --> 00:02:45,233
the third option is using normal mode precision assembler

57
00:02:45,233 --> 00:02:47,433
we crafted last episode

58
00:02:48,133 --> 00:02:50,800
the issue was that the casings of its structure

59
00:02:50,800 --> 00:02:53,500
required an LuV assembler to be crafted

60
00:02:54,466 --> 00:02:54,966
however

61
00:02:54,966 --> 00:02:57,600
if we want it to work in normal mode

62
00:02:57,600 --> 00:03:01,700
we can use the lower tier casings, the imprecise ones

63
00:03:01,800 --> 00:03:05,300
that way the assembler will fully live to its name

64
00:03:06,500 --> 00:03:08,300
after preparing the patterns

65
00:03:08,300 --> 00:03:12,100
we craft just the minimal amount required to form the structure

66
00:03:12,433 --> 00:03:14,633
and to make that thing work fast

67
00:03:14,633 --> 00:03:17,466
we shall have a 16 amps energy hatch

68
00:03:17,600 --> 00:03:18,233
that way

69
00:03:18,233 --> 00:03:22,033
it will work twice as fast as 16 IV assemblers

70
00:03:23,000 --> 00:03:26,366
and you can already see how charging its personal buffer

71
00:03:26,366 --> 00:03:28,300
takes a toll on our main battery

72
00:03:28,733 --> 00:03:30,300
once everything is ready

73
00:03:30,300 --> 00:03:32,466
we assemble the assembler structure

74
00:03:32,633 --> 00:03:36,333
we fill all the non-mandatory casings with cheap buses

75
00:03:36,600 --> 00:03:38,633
and now we can turn that thing on

76
00:03:38,633 --> 00:03:42,466
and see how little it takes now to make hundreds of SMDs

77
00:03:43,233 --> 00:03:45,833
the last bottleneck is our circuit assemblers

78
00:03:45,866 --> 00:03:47,500
so we add a couple more

79
00:03:47,933 --> 00:03:49,900
one for each circuit step

80
00:03:50,266 --> 00:03:53,333
and then we can take a break and AFK a bit

81
00:03:54,933 --> 00:03:58,300
or maybe we could just farm more nether stars

82
00:03:59,433 --> 00:04:00,933
after the quick break

83
00:04:00,933 --> 00:04:02,800
our assembly line is ready

84
00:04:03,533 --> 00:04:06,500
this multi block can be built with different lengths

85
00:04:06,733 --> 00:04:10,533
every additional slice adds space for one more input item

86
00:04:11,800 --> 00:04:13,900
we can also rotate it using a wrench

87
00:04:13,900 --> 00:04:17,033
to build it vertically and have it use less space

88
00:04:18,633 --> 00:04:19,533
and for the moment

89
00:04:19,533 --> 00:04:22,000
we are going to build one of medium length

90
00:04:23,500 --> 00:04:25,100
we quickly add the energy input

91
00:04:25,100 --> 00:04:26,800
and then we move to the bottom

92
00:04:26,833 --> 00:04:30,033
where we will have to plan a way of automating that thing

93
00:04:31,066 --> 00:04:33,866
since each items goes in a different slice

94
00:04:33,866 --> 00:04:37,066
we use the smallest buses to push items up

95
00:04:38,733 --> 00:04:40,266
to fill the items in

96
00:04:40,300 --> 00:04:45,466
we use a dedicated ae2 network where we drop items inside an interface

97
00:04:45,466 --> 00:04:48,600
and they get moved with storage buses to the machine

98
00:04:50,600 --> 00:04:54,033
and if we do not want things to go into random places

99
00:04:54,033 --> 00:04:57,033
we have to sort the storage buses priorities

100
00:04:58,433 --> 00:05:01,466
we are not sorting the items with a filtering mechanism

101
00:05:01,466 --> 00:05:06,400
because many recipes require the same items but in a different location layout

102
00:05:07,800 --> 00:05:10,700
once we have fully configured the priorities

103
00:05:10,700 --> 00:05:13,533
we add an interface connected to our main network

104
00:05:13,533 --> 00:05:16,133
to automate the crafting requests

105
00:05:17,933 --> 00:05:20,433
now we can slip inside a crafting pattern

106
00:05:20,433 --> 00:05:22,833
and see if everything works as expected

107
00:05:24,300 --> 00:05:26,500
once all the materials are prepared

108
00:05:26,500 --> 00:05:29,300
they are correctly inserted into the slots

109
00:05:30,533 --> 00:05:34,000
however once we tried to turn on the assembly line

110
00:05:34,000 --> 00:05:36,300
we realize we have forgotten something

111
00:05:37,666 --> 00:05:39,833
other than the crafting materials

112
00:05:39,833 --> 00:05:44,033
the machine also need the instructions on how to build things

113
00:05:44,466 --> 00:05:45,533
to get those

114
00:05:45,533 --> 00:05:50,266
we have to do some research by scanning the lower tier of the thing we want to assemble

115
00:05:50,633 --> 00:05:53,266
we quickly move to our EV scanner to do that

116
00:05:53,266 --> 00:05:54,233
and we find out

117
00:05:54,233 --> 00:05:58,600
it will take a quarter of hour to get the instructions for our assembly line

118
00:05:59,266 --> 00:06:02,466
and we have to do that for every Luv component

119
00:06:04,000 --> 00:06:06,633
anyways once our research is done

120
00:06:06,633 --> 00:06:09,066
we can bring the data to the assembly line

121
00:06:09,066 --> 00:06:11,066
which will finally start working

122
00:06:12,833 --> 00:06:15,000
one motor is almost useless

123
00:06:15,000 --> 00:06:17,200
so we shall start crafting more

124
00:06:18,533 --> 00:06:21,500
but while it looked like everything was fine

125
00:06:21,500 --> 00:06:24,033
one big issue was starting to build up

126
00:06:25,066 --> 00:06:27,866
the items are being pushed to the assembly line

127
00:06:27,900 --> 00:06:30,433
and since some buses were already filled

128
00:06:30,466 --> 00:06:33,200
the overflow went to the wrong input slices

129
00:06:34,600 --> 00:06:36,100
to avoid such thing

130
00:06:36,100 --> 00:06:39,733
we have to add a blocking card to the assembly line network

131
00:06:40,866 --> 00:06:44,133
and enable blocking mode on the interface with a pattern

132
00:06:45,433 --> 00:06:45,933
and with that

133
00:06:45,933 --> 00:06:49,100
we can see that the motors are being crafted one at a time

134
00:06:49,100 --> 00:06:51,533
with everything being perfectly dosed

135
00:06:52,833 --> 00:06:54,900
now we can scan the other components

136
00:06:54,900 --> 00:06:57,233
and bring the data to the assembly line

137
00:06:57,400 --> 00:06:57,833
however

138
00:06:57,833 --> 00:07:01,433
there is only one space in the assembly line controller

139
00:07:03,233 --> 00:07:05,100
but we can add a data access hatch

140
00:07:05,100 --> 00:07:06,666
to increase that amount

141
00:07:08,800 --> 00:07:09,933
the next issue is that

142
00:07:09,933 --> 00:07:12,300
some components have too many ingredients

143
00:07:12,300 --> 00:07:14,233
to fit our pattern terminal

144
00:07:15,833 --> 00:07:16,733
of those

145
00:07:16,733 --> 00:07:19,300
we manually craft just the bare minimum amount

146
00:07:19,300 --> 00:07:23,933
to upgrade our pattern terminal to a fluid processing pattern terminal

147
00:07:25,033 --> 00:07:28,433
this one has 32 input slots instead of nine

148
00:07:28,500 --> 00:07:31,466
more than enough for any assembly line recipe

149
00:07:32,733 --> 00:07:34,633
we quickly drop in the new patterns

150
00:07:34,633 --> 00:07:37,266
and now we can move on to the next quest

151
00:07:37,900 --> 00:07:41,533
which is probably going to be in the previous tier

152
00:07:41,533 --> 00:07:44,333
to reach new planets with new materials

153
00:07:45,233 --> 00:07:47,466
and that means crafting a new rocket

154
00:07:47,466 --> 00:07:50,833
whose plates must now be assembled in an assembly line

155
00:07:52,066 --> 00:07:54,900
we quickly set up the new crafting patterns

156
00:07:54,900 --> 00:07:57,000
but then we run into a new issue

157
00:07:57,833 --> 00:07:59,033
everything got stuck

158
00:07:59,033 --> 00:08:02,133
because the plates did not split into the two buses

159
00:08:03,400 --> 00:08:04,666
to fix that issue

160
00:08:04,666 --> 00:08:07,400
we are going to use one simple solution

161
00:08:07,400 --> 00:08:12,666
we prepare some molds that will rename the parts before sending them to the assembly line

162
00:08:13,900 --> 00:08:14,466
to use it

163
00:08:14,466 --> 00:08:15,900
we make a pattern that

164
00:08:15,900 --> 00:08:18,866
with help of a press and the previously made mold

165
00:08:18,866 --> 00:08:20,700
will rename the items

166
00:08:22,066 --> 00:08:23,733
now we can edit the plate pattern

167
00:08:23,733 --> 00:08:27,066
to use the two different items that won't merge

168
00:08:28,533 --> 00:08:29,466
and with that

169
00:08:29,466 --> 00:08:34,033
we can now start making complex assembly line recipes in an easy way

170
00:08:35,833 --> 00:08:38,200
once everything is in the correct place

171
00:08:38,200 --> 00:08:41,033
we can start crafting our rocket plates

172
00:08:41,900 --> 00:08:44,600
which we use to make the tier 4 rocket

173
00:08:45,133 --> 00:08:46,833
while that is being built

174
00:08:46,833 --> 00:08:49,533
we can also prepare a new kind of miner

175
00:08:49,533 --> 00:08:51,000
the ore drilling plant

176
00:08:52,066 --> 00:08:55,500
that is the multi block version of the small miners

177
00:08:55,500 --> 00:08:56,633
it has several buffs

178
00:08:56,633 --> 00:08:58,733
but it requires to move a bigger structure

179
00:08:58,733 --> 00:09:00,866
and need drilling fluid to work

180
00:09:01,800 --> 00:09:03,433
and while that is crafting

181
00:09:03,466 --> 00:09:06,200
we can get a better tool for locating minerals

182
00:09:06,200 --> 00:09:07,733
an electric prospector

183
00:09:08,900 --> 00:09:12,933
this thing can also be used to check the pollution in our base

184
00:09:14,066 --> 00:09:18,433
but its main usage is to see the disposition of underground resources

185
00:09:19,233 --> 00:09:21,800
and once we locate a good mining spot

186
00:09:21,800 --> 00:09:24,000
we can build the ore drilling plant

187
00:09:24,666 --> 00:09:28,000
which is going to mine all the minerals in a huge area

188
00:09:28,000 --> 00:09:30,533
one chunk at a time layer by layer

189
00:09:31,700 --> 00:09:34,666
and to avoid getting overwhelmed by its output

190
00:09:34,666 --> 00:09:38,600
we can throttle it by decreasing the amount of drilling fluid we send

191
00:09:39,733 --> 00:09:43,466
and now we are ready to start working on the LuV tier

192
00:09:43,500 --> 00:09:45,900
but that's for the next episode

193
00:09:45,933 --> 00:09:46,900
bye bye

194
00:00:00,333 --> 00:00:01,366
欢迎回来！

195
00:00:01,366 --> 00:00:04,833
今天我们要进入 LuV 级电压

196
00:00:05,066 --> 00:00:05,666
想达成目标

197
00:00:05,666 --> 00:00:09,400
当务之急便是一条装配线

198
00:00:09,533 --> 00:00:13,000
这个多方块结构使用起来相当复杂

199
00:00:13,300 --> 00:00:16,266
不过先让我们从结构方块开始

200
00:00:16,533 --> 00:00:19,666
这些组件制作起来既不轻松又不便宜

201
00:00:19,666 --> 00:00:23,400
甚至连 AE 自动下单都成了问题

202
00:00:23,500 --> 00:00:24,800
主要问题是

203
00:00:24,800 --> 00:00:29,133
我们的合成存储单元的空间出现了短缺

204
00:00:29,133 --> 00:00:31,866
所以我们先做一些存储元件

205
00:00:32,300 --> 00:00:35,266
同时也得来点并行单元

206
00:00:35,266 --> 00:00:37,333
来加快制作过程

207
00:00:37,866 --> 00:00:41,900
AE 的合成 CPU 升级过后

208
00:00:41,900 --> 00:00:45,800
我们终于可以开始生产装配线所需的材料了

209
00:00:46,200 --> 00:00:48,266
这需要一些时间

210
00:00:48,266 --> 00:00:49,866
所以我们可以忙里偷闲做些其他事

211
00:00:49,866 --> 00:00:52,333
比如刷些凋零

212
00:00:52,633 --> 00:00:55,133
下界之星可是未来必需品

213
00:00:55,600 --> 00:00:58,033
然而经过短暂的刷怪时间

214
00:00:58,033 --> 00:00:58,900
我们发现

215
00:00:58,900 --> 00:01:01,866
装配线的制作似乎没什么进展

216
00:01:02,400 --> 00:01:04,266
主要问题是

217
00:01:04,266 --> 00:01:07,366
并行单元发配材料的速度跟不上

218
00:01:07,366 --> 00:01:09,900
各个机器的处理速度

219
00:01:10,333 --> 00:01:13,000
我们可以增加并行单元

220
00:01:13,033 --> 00:01:17,700
但最好的解决方案是减少 CPU 必须完成的任务量

221
00:01:18,400 --> 00:01:21,633
我们可以将样板中的材料全部倍增

222
00:01:21,633 --> 00:01:22,133
所以说

223
00:01:22,133 --> 00:01:25,733
CPU 不会发配 64 次单个矿粉

224
00:01:25,733 --> 00:01:29,033
而是一次性发配 64 个矿粉

225
00:01:29,800 --> 00:01:31,266
正好在高炉旁边

226
00:01:31,266 --> 00:01:34,300
我们顺便给它升级更好的线圈

227
00:01:34,300 --> 00:01:36,866
有效提升它的并行

228
00:01:37,700 --> 00:01:41,066
在倍增样板、重新下单后

229
00:01:41,066 --> 00:01:42,733
我们可以看到各类原材料

230
00:01:42,733 --> 00:01:45,733
被发配到机器的速度差异

231
00:01:47,000 --> 00:01:49,200
没过多久

232
00:01:49,200 --> 00:01:52,233
我们看到处理单元闲置了

233
00:01:52,800 --> 00:01:53,700
原因是

234
00:01:53,700 --> 00:01:58,066
我们正在一个小组装机中制作数千个贴片元件

235
00:01:58,333 --> 00:01:59,833
一批做16个

236
00:02:00,466 --> 00:02:03,500
每批也需要相当长的时间

237
00:02:04,533 --> 00:02:07,666
我们已经将制作压力分配给不同的组装机

238
00:02:07,700 --> 00:02:10,266
但效果并不明显

239
00:02:10,600 --> 00:02:14,400
即使四个组装机应该比单个快四倍

240
00:02:15,333 --> 00:02:17,433
但我们可以用更高级的组装机

241
00:02:17,433 --> 00:02:20,433
但耗电会指数级增长

242
00:02:20,933 --> 00:02:22,633
所以我们需要一个多方块组装机

243
00:02:23,033 --> 00:02:24,933
第一个选项是 GT++ 的

244
00:02:25,600 --> 00:02:30,200
但那需要我们目前无法制作的 ZPM 材料

245
00:02:30,533 --> 00:02:35,700
第二种选择是在处理阵列中堆组装机

246
00:02:36,233 --> 00:02:37,000
然而

247
00:02:37,000 --> 00:02:38,633
在我们需要升级它的时候

248
00:02:38,633 --> 00:02:41,066
它扩展性较差

249
00:02:42,066 --> 00:02:45,233
第三种选择是使用我们上一集制作的

250
00:02:45,233 --> 00:02:47,433
精密组装机的常规模式

251
00:02:48,133 --> 00:02:50,800
问题是它的机械外壳

252
00:02:50,800 --> 00:02:53,500
需要 LuV 组装机制作

253
00:02:54,466 --> 00:02:54,966
然而

254
00:02:54,966 --> 00:02:57,600
如果我们想让它在常规模式下工作

255
00:02:57,600 --> 00:03:01,700
我们可以用不精密的电子机械方块

256
00:03:01,800 --> 00:03:05,300
这样精密组装机将完全名副其实

257
00:03:06,500 --> 00:03:08,300
准备好样板后

258
00:03:08,300 --> 00:03:12,100
我们只准备能构成结构的最少材料

259
00:03:12,433 --> 00:03:14,633
为了让那东西快速工作

260
00:03:14,633 --> 00:03:17,466
我们将安装一个 16A 能源仓

261
00:03:17,600 --> 00:03:18,233
由此

262
00:03:18,233 --> 00:03:22,033
它比 16 联 IV 组装机快两倍

263
00:03:23,000 --> 00:03:26,366
你们可以看到为这个电池组充电

264
00:03:26,366 --> 00:03:28,300
已经对主电网产生巨大威胁

265
00:03:28,733 --> 00:03:30,300
一切准备就绪后

266
00:03:30,300 --> 00:03:32,466
我们安装好精密组装机

267
00:03:32,633 --> 00:03:36,333
我们使用廉价的低级输入仓替代结构方块

268
00:03:36,600 --> 00:03:38,633
现在我们开机

269
00:03:38,633 --> 00:03:42,466
看到做几百个贴片电容轻而易举

270
00:03:43,233 --> 00:03:45,833
最后一个瓶颈是电路组装机

271
00:03:45,866 --> 00:03:47,500
所以我们再加几台机器

272
00:03:47,933 --> 00:03:49,900
给每个电路制作步骤来一个

273
00:03:50,266 --> 00:03:53,333
然后我们便可以小憩片刻，挂会机

274
00:03:54,933 --> 00:03:58,300
或者说再去刷些下界之星

275
00:03:59,433 --> 00:04:00,933
快速休息后

276
00:04:00,933 --> 00:04:02,800
我们的装配线已经准备好了

277
00:04:03,533 --> 00:04:06,500
这个多方块结构可以由不同长度构成

278
00:04:06,733 --> 00:04:10,533
每额外片都将额外增加一个输入空间

279
00:04:11,800 --> 00:04:13,900
我们也可以用扳手旋转它

280
00:04:13,900 --> 00:04:17,033
垂直建造来节省空间

281
00:04:18,633 --> 00:04:19,533
就目前而言

282
00:04:19,533 --> 00:04:22,000
一个中等长度的就不赖

283
00:04:23,500 --> 00:04:25,100
我们快速添加能源仓

284
00:04:25,100 --> 00:04:26,800
然后移动到底部

285
00:04:26,833 --> 00:04:30,033
开始准备自动化装配线

286
00:04:31,066 --> 00:04:33,866
因为每个输入物都在不同的片层

287
00:04:33,866 --> 00:04:37,066
我们将使用输入总线(ULV)

288
00:04:38,733 --> 00:04:40,266
为了进行输入

289
00:04:40,300 --> 00:04:45,466
我们把主网配方材料发配进子网

290
00:04:45,466 --> 00:04:48,600
子网通过存储总线转移物品进机器

291
00:04:50,600 --> 00:04:54,033
如果我们不想让物品随机排列

292
00:04:54,033 --> 00:04:57,033
必须对存储总线的优先级进行排序

293
00:04:58,433 --> 00:05:01,466
我们不会使用白名单来进行物品过滤

294
00:05:01,466 --> 00:05:06,400
因为许多配方在不同的位置使用相同的物品

295
00:05:07,800 --> 00:05:10,700
一旦我们配置好了优先级

296
00:05:10,700 --> 00:05:13,533
便可以通过一个接口与我们主网相连

297
00:05:13,533 --> 00:05:16,133
来完成自动化下单

298
00:05:17,933 --> 00:05:20,433
现在可以往里面塞入一个样板

299
00:05:20,433 --> 00:05:22,833
看看一切是否按预期进行

300
00:05:24,300 --> 00:05:26,500
一旦所有的材料都准备好了

301
00:05:26,500 --> 00:05:29,300
它们被正确放入输入总线中

302
00:05:30,533 --> 00:05:34,000
然而，一旦我们试图开启装配线

303
00:05:34,000 --> 00:05:36,300
我们发现忘记了什么

304
00:05:37,666 --> 00:05:39,833
除了制作材料

305
00:05:39,833 --> 00:05:44,033
机器还需要知道怎么去造

306
00:05:44,466 --> 00:05:45,533
来完成这个目标

307
00:05:45,533 --> 00:05:50,266
我们要研究其下级材料来获得研究结果

308
00:05:50,633 --> 00:05:53,266
我们火速去 EV 扫描机做研究

309
00:05:53,266 --> 00:05:54,233
我们发现

310
00:05:54,233 --> 00:05:58,600
得到装配线的研究结果要一刻钟

311
00:05:59,266 --> 00:06:02,466
而每个 LuV 组件都得经过这个过程

312
00:06:04,000 --> 00:06:06,633
不管怎样，一旦我们的研究结束

313
00:06:06,633 --> 00:06:09,066
我们把研究结果放进装配线

314
00:06:09,066 --> 00:06:11,066
装配线终于开始工作了

315
00:06:12,833 --> 00:06:15,000
一个马达没什么用处

316
00:06:15,000 --> 00:06:17,200
我们要多做点

317
00:06:18,533 --> 00:06:21,500
虽然一切看上去安然无恙

318
00:06:21,500 --> 00:06:24,033
但一个大问题开始浮出水面

319
00:06:25,066 --> 00:06:27,866
所有物品都被发配到装配线上

320
00:06:27,900 --> 00:06:30,433
因为有些输入总线已经被填满

321
00:06:30,466 --> 00:06:33,200
导致其溢出至错误的切片中

322
00:06:34,600 --> 00:06:36,100
为了避免发生这样的事情

323
00:06:36,100 --> 00:06:39,733
我们得给装配线网络加一个高级阻挡卡

324
00:06:40,866 --> 00:06:44,133
并在接口中开启高级阻挡模式

325
00:06:45,433 --> 00:06:45,933
有了这个

326
00:06:45,933 --> 00:06:49,100
我们看到一次只会制作一个马达

327
00:06:49,100 --> 00:06:51,533
物品的发配数量非常完美

328
00:06:52,833 --> 00:06:54,900
现在我们可以扫描其他组件了

329
00:06:54,900 --> 00:06:57,233
并将研究结果带到装配线

330
00:06:57,400 --> 00:06:57,833
然而

331
00:06:57,833 --> 00:07:01,433
装配线控制器中只有一个空槽

332
00:07:03,233 --> 00:07:05,100
但我们可以添加一个数据访问舱口

333
00:07:05,100 --> 00:07:06,666
来增加数据数量

334
00:07:08,800 --> 00:07:09,933
下一个问题是

335
00:07:09,933 --> 00:07:12,300
有些样板所写入的材料太多

336
00:07:12,300 --> 00:07:14,233
当前的样板终端无法胜任

337
00:07:15,833 --> 00:07:16,733
对那些物品

338
00:07:16,733 --> 00:07:19,300
我们手动制作出最少的量

339
00:07:19,300 --> 00:07:23,933
来升级至增广流体样板终端

340
00:07:25,033 --> 00:07:28,433
它有 32 个写入栏，而非 9 个

341
00:07:28,500 --> 00:07:31,466
对于任何装配线配方来说都绰绰有余

342
00:07:32,733 --> 00:07:34,633
我们快速写好新样板

343
00:07:34,633 --> 00:07:37,266
然后继续做下一个任务

344
00:07:37,900 --> 00:07:41,533
任务在上一电压

345
00:07:41,533 --> 00:07:44,333
去往具有新材料的新星球

346
00:07:45,233 --> 00:07:47,466
这意味着制造一枚新火箭

347
00:07:47,466 --> 00:07:50,833
而它的装甲板必须在装配线上制造

348
00:07:52,066 --> 00:07:54,900
马上写好样板

349
00:07:54,900 --> 00:07:57,000
但我们遇到了一个新问题

350
00:07:57,833 --> 00:07:59,033
所有东西都卡住了

351
00:07:59,033 --> 00:08:02,133
因为对应板没有均分进两片

352
00:08:03,400 --> 00:08:04,666
为了解决这个问题

353
00:08:04,666 --> 00:08:07,400
我们将使用一个简单的解决方案

354
00:08:07,400 --> 00:08:12,666
用模具来重命名要送入装配线的物品

355
00:08:13,900 --> 00:08:14,466
来使用它重命名材料

356
00:08:14,466 --> 00:08:15,900
我们写了一个样板

357
00:08:15,900 --> 00:08:18,866
在冲压机床和之前的模具的帮助下

358
00:08:18,866 --> 00:08:20,700
材料将被重命名

359
00:08:22,066 --> 00:08:23,733
现在我们可以重新编辑样板了

360
00:08:23,733 --> 00:08:27,066
使用不会合并的两个物品

361
00:08:28,533 --> 00:08:29,466
有了这个

362
00:08:29,466 --> 00:08:34,033
我们以简单的方式制作复杂的装配线配方

363
00:08:35,833 --> 00:08:38,200
一旦一切都在正确的地方

364
00:08:38,200 --> 00:08:41,033
我们开始制作火箭板

365
00:08:41,900 --> 00:08:44,600
我们将其用来制作 T4 火箭

366
00:08:45,133 --> 00:08:46,833
在制造的同时

367
00:08:46,833 --> 00:08:49,533
我们还可以准备一种新型矿机

368
00:08:49,533 --> 00:08:51,000
采矿厂

369
00:08:52,066 --> 00:08:55,500
它是小矿机的多方块版本

370
00:08:55,500 --> 00:08:56,633
它有几点增强

371
00:08:56,633 --> 00:08:58,733
但它需要一个更大的结构

372
00:08:58,733 --> 00:09:00,866
并且需要钻井液才能工作

373
00:09:01,800 --> 00:09:03,433
在制作的同时

374
00:09:03,466 --> 00:09:06,200
我们找到更好定位矿物的工具

375
00:09:06,200 --> 00:09:07,733
探矿仪

376
00:09:08,900 --> 00:09:12,933
这东西也可以用来检查基地的污染情况

377
00:09:14,066 --> 00:09:18,433
但它的主要用途是查看地下资源的配置

378
00:09:19,233 --> 00:09:21,800
一旦我们找到一个好的矿脉点

379
00:09:21,800 --> 00:09:24,000
我们建造采矿厂

380
00:09:24,666 --> 00:09:28,000
来开采一大片区块的所有矿物

381
00:09:28,000 --> 00:09:30,533
逐区块、逐层地运行

382
00:09:31,700 --> 00:09:34,666
为避免被其输出物压垮

383
00:09:34,666 --> 00:09:38,600
我们可以减少钻井液供应来控制它

384
00:09:39,733 --> 00:09:43,466
现在我们可以推 LuV 的进度了

385
00:09:43,500 --> 00:09:45,900
但那得是下一集的内容了

386
00:09:45,933 --> 00:09:46,900
拜拜

387
00:02:30,533 --> 00:02:35,700
（正式版已废弃）

388
00:04:54,033 --> 00:04:57,033
（使用优先卡可以快速完成这工作）

389
00:06:36,100 --> 00:06:39,733
（高级阻挡卡将物品检测拓展到它在的整个 ME 网络）

